# Study Bible dark palette & UI chrome

Use **`src/lib/theme/study-bible-dark.ts`** as the single source of truth. Do not invent new purple-gray hex values for dark surfaces; extend the palette there if a new token is truly needed.

## Core palette (hex reference)

| Role | Hex | Notes |
|------|-----|--------|
| Page / app backdrop | `#24231f` | Default dark page |
| Surfaces | `#30283c`, `#342a43`, `#3b3348`, `#2a2534`, `#272133`, `#463b55` | Used by cards + **hashed** drawer shades |
| Border / divider | `#1c1921` | Hairline borders; avoid extra **border-b** under drawer titles unless explicitly specced |
| Accent / interactive | `#80778e` | Active states, drawer handle, selected calendar day |
| Foreground | `#fffaff` | Primary text |
| Muted / secondary text | `#ded6e7`, `#cfc5db` | Labels, descriptions |
| Purple accent | `#563985` | Sparingly (legacy accent) |
| **Light primary chrome** | `#6b5196` | FAB/menu (`fabMenuPrimary`), phone bottom nav (`navBar`), **data table headers** (`tableHeader`) |
| Light primary hover | `#5c4685` | FAB hover; table/nav header borders (`border-[#5c4685]/40`) |

## `studyBibleDarkClasses` (semantic Tailwind bundles)

Import `studyBibleDarkClasses` and pick by **purpose** — keeps cards and list chrome consistent:

- **`page`** — full-page dark shell text/bg.
- **`bwiCard`**, **`callsCard`**, **`todoCard`** — section cards (BWI vs Calls vs To-Do list cards); borders + surface differ slightly by tier.
- **`summaryCard`** — summary/metrics strips.
- **`header`** / **`callsHeader`** — interactive header bars (use sparingly; prefer flat panel + shade).
- **`muted`** / **`subtle`** / **`callsMuted`** — secondary copy on dark surfaces.
- **`divider`** — horizontal rules when a divider is intentional.
- **`tableHeader`** / **`tableHeaderRow`** / **`tableHeaderSortButton*`** — fixed list/table column headers. Light mode header fill **`#6b5196`** (aligned with **`fabMenuPrimary`**); body rows use **`tableBody`** + per-row **`getStudyBibleDarkCardShade`**. See **`.cursor/rules/mobile-table-bwi-design.mdc`**.
- **`navBar`** — phone bottom nav; light mode also **`#6b5196`**.

Prefer these over one-off `dark:bg-[#…]` on cards unless matching an existing sibling component.

## Hashed surfaces: `getStudyBibleDarkCardShade` / `getStudyBibleDarkCardFade`

- **`getStudyBibleDarkCardShade(key: string)`** returns one of six stable **`dark:bg-[#…]`** classes. The index is derived from **`key` via hashing** (not `Math.random()`), so the same key always gets the same tint across sessions.
- **`getStudyBibleDarkCardFade(key)`** — gradient fade variants for hero/list edges when needed.

**Key naming:** Use stable, descriptive strings, e.g. `bwi-calls-list-drawer:${userId}`, `bwi-todos-filter-drawer:${scopeKey}`, `bwi-visit-filters-call-date`. Include **user or scope** when the panel is user/data-scoped so different panels don’t accidentally share the same hue if you change keys later.

**Usage:** Merge onto shells with `cn()`:

```ts
cn("dark:border-[#1c1921] dark:text-[#fffaff]", getStudyBibleDarkCardShade(`my-panel:${userId}`))
```

Avoid stacking another full **`dark:bg-[#181714]`** (or similar flat gray) **on top of** a shade unless you need a nested inset; the shade **is** the panel background.

## Drawers (bottom sheets, left filter sheets, wide right/left panels)

**Phone bottom sheets with inputs:** use **`FormDrawerRoot`** + **`FormDrawerContent`** (or **`FormModal`**) and scroll padding from **`form-drawer-phone.ts`** — see **`.cursor/rules/ios-viewport-safe-area.mdc`** (Drawer form sheets).

1. **Panel** — `dark:border-[#1c1921]`, **`dark:text-[#fffaff]`**, plus **`getStudyBibleDarkCardShade(key)`** for main `DrawerContent` / `DrawerWideLeftContent` / `DrawerWideRightContent` / `DrawerThinRightContent` surfaces.
2. **Title row** — Prefer **`DrawerHeader`** with **`bg-transparent`** (and **`shrink-0`** where needed) so the header doesn’t read as a separate “strip.” **Do not** default to **`border-b border-border`** on drawer titles; spacing (`pt` / `pb` / `gap`) carries hierarchy.
3. **Handle** (bottom sheets) — Optional: `handleClassName` with muted lavender handle + soft shadow (see **CallHistory** / **HomeTodoCard**) for consistency.
4. **Scroll layout** — Outer: **`flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col`**; inner scroll: **`min-h-0 flex-1 overflow-y-auto`** with bottom safe padding **`pb-[calc(max(env(safe-area-inset-bottom),0px)+80px)]`** where FAB/nav overlaps.
5. **Nested date/filter sheets** — Reuse the same **`DateRangeSelectContent`** + thin right drawer / modal pattern as **VisitFiltersForm** (call date / due date); palette key like `bwi-visit-filters-call-date` for the nested drawer.

## Cards & lists inside dark sections

- Use **`studyBibleDarkClasses`** for bordered list/card containers (**`bwiCard`**, **`todoCard`**, etc.) per section.
- Secondary labels: **`studyBibleDarkClasses.muted`** (not ad-hoc `opacity-*` on white).
- **Establishment / householder status** colors: always **`STATUS_HIERARCHY`** helpers from **`src/lib/utils/status-hierarchy.ts`** — never duplicate status colors in local components.

## Checklist when adding a new dark drawer or card

- [ ] Shade or semantic class from **`study-bible-dark`**, not a one-off hex unless adding a token.
- [ ] Stable **`key`** string for **`getStudyBibleDarkCardShade`** if the shell should vary per user/scope.
- [ ] Header **`bg-transparent`** unless design explicitly needs a contrasting sub-bar.
- [ ] No redundant **border-b** between title and toolbar/filter row.
- [ ] Mobile-first layout; tablet-only changes via **`md:`** per **`mobile-first-tablet-layout`**.

## App shell & panel placement (viewport)

- **Mobile-first (default, viewports below `768px`):** Auxiliary panels opened from section cards (e.g. **Calls** full history, **Contacts** full list, filters) use **bottom drawers** only (`FormModal` / `DrawerContent` from the bottom). Do not use left/right edge sheets as the primary pattern on phone.
- **iPad / tablet (`md:` and up):** When **`preferLeftDetailPanel`** (or equivalent) applies, those full lists open as **left edge sheets** beside the main detail content. The overall app shell on tablet is **sidebar + bottom bar** (main nav); section cards stay consistent with **Calls** / **Contacts** (tappable header + chevron, preview rows, full list in the sheet).
